casebody.data:
THE CITY OF NEWARK, A MUNICIPAL CORPORATION, PETITIONER, v. HONORABLE CHARLES W. PARKER, A JUSTICE OF THE NEW JERSEY SUPREME COURT, WARREN DIXON, Jr., WILLIAM K. FLANAGAN, HAROLD A. PRICE AND ANDREW J. STEELMAN, RESPONDENTS. Argued November 23, 1937 Decided December 16, 1937.

Before Justices Bodine, Heher and Perskie.

For the petitioner, James F. X. O’Brien. For the respondents, Warren Dixon, Jr., William F. Flanagan, Harold A. Price and Andrew J. Steelman, pro se. *227Per Curiam.

We have considered with care the arguments made before us and the briefs submitted, aud we can only conclude that no debatable questions exist which have not been disposed of in the eases relied upon by Mr. Justice Parker in the memorandum filed by him and printed herewith.

The writ will be denied.
